The first term is the inertia matrix formula_172 relative to the center of mass. The second and third terms are zero by definition of the center of mass formula_116. And the last term is the total mass of the system multiplied by the square of the skew-symmetric matrix formula_218 constructed from formula_211.

The result is the parallel axis theorem,
